---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Farlink Systems is built around field-tested electrical and automation work for industrial, commercial, water, and government facilities.">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>Field experience first.</h1>
      <p>
        Farlink Systems came out of hands-on electrical and automation work. The company exists to solve real problems at real
        sites, not to dress up ordinary work with fancy language.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          We have worked on controls, power, testing, commissioning, and troubleshooting in industrial plants, water and
          wastewater facilities, commercial sites, and government projects.
        </p>
        <p>
          That background changes how we approach the work. We care about whether the drawings are usable, whether the scope is
          actually clear, and whether the system will start up without turning into a finger-pointing exercise.
        </p>
        <p>
          Good engineering should make the job easier for operations, maintenance, and the owner. That is the bar.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <article class="card info-card">
          <span class="eyebrow">Platforms</span>
          <ul class="list-reset checklist compact-list">
            <li>Allen Bradley / Rockwell</li>
            <li>CODESYS</li>
            <li>FactoryTalk View</li>
            <li>Other HMI and controls platforms as needed</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card">
          <span class="eyebrow">Typical sectors</span>
          <ul class="list-reset checklist compact-list">
            <li>Industrial and manufacturing</li>
            <li>Water and wastewater</li>
            <li>Commercial facilities</li>
            <li>Government and public infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--muted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">What that means in practice</span>
        <h2>We try to make the work easier for the people who have to live with it.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid info-grid--3">
        <article class="card info-card">
          <span class="eyebrow">Process first</span>
          <p>We start with the production goal, site limitations, and outage windows before we talk about solutions.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card">
          <span class="eyebrow">Usable documents</span>
          <p>Drawings, scopes, and study outputs should help the next person do their job instead of slowing them down.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card info-card">
          <span class="eyebrow">Direct communication</span>
          <p>Clients should know what is happening, what decisions matter, and what still needs to be resolved.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="surface callout">
        <span class="eyebrow">Need a hand?</span>
        <p>
          Some clients bring us in early to shape a project. Others call when something already exists and is not working well.
          Both are fine.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a href="/services" class="btn">See services</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--ghost">Start a conversation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .compact-list {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 860px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(280px, 0.8fr);
    }
  }
</style>
